  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Let <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>g</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> be a closed Riemannian manifold of dimension <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>n</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>3</mn></math> and let <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>f</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∞</mo></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>M</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , such that the operator <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>f</mi></math> is positive. If g is flat near some point p and f vanishes around p , we can define the mass of <math altimg="si13.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub></math> as the constant term in the expansion of the Green function of <math altimg="si13.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub></math> at p . In this paper, we establish many results on the mass of such operators. In particular, if <math altimg="si6.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mfrac><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></msub></math> , i.e. if <math altimg="si13.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub></math> is the Yamabe operator, we show the following result: assume that there exists a closed simply connected non-spin manifold M such that the mass is non-negative for every metric g as above on M , then the mass is non-negative for every such metric on every closed manifold of the same dimension as M .</subfield>
